CALL OF DUTY MOBILE OUT NOW ON IOS, ANDROID GETS IT SOON
≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈↓↓↓↓≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈≈
While Call of Duty: Modern Warfare's October 25 release on PC, PlayStation 4, and Xbox One approaches, publisher Activision has announced that a mobile version of its popular first-person shooter is available now on iOS.

Call of Duty (Mobile) is a free-to-play CoD experience “brimming with content” from both the Black Ops and Modern Warfare series, according to a press release from earlier this month. It is said to feature a fully-customizable control scheme, multiple game types, well-known characters and weapons, and a Battle Royale mode. The game is currently available now on iOS devices, with Android launching sometime soon. Activision previously stated that Call of Duty: Mobile will launch on both Android and iOS on October 1, so Android users should expect it soon.

caption.text:
Recently picked up the vinyl soundtrack for Red Dead Redemption 2.
.
I'm not usually a buyer of vinyls but I went with the Ultimate Edition of the game with the collectors box so thought I'd go and get the limited edition soundtrack to go with it.
.
It's a fantastic game that I'm still playing. I have finished the main story but there are so many other side missions and challenges I've still not hit 90% complete.
.
Did anyone else get the vinyl soundtrack?
.

So if you’re looking for some cool products straight from Japan give these guys a checkout. You might find something up your alley.

caption.text:
My first impressions of the N-Switch game controller from Ipega are surprisingly positive. I was interested in it because it was a mix of third party joycons, which I mainly wanted for better chances with the controls sticks, and a Switch grip that would not only make handheld mode more comfortable but also offer more support to the connection points on the side when holding it.
.
I played Yooka-Laylee for a few hours with it tonight and despite it not having a full back like I thought it did, it still is surprisingly supportive yet lightweight. The layout is a tad awkward but I adjusted to it fine and the feel is decent. The buttons definitely feel strange and the d-pad is a little stiff, but the sticks are actually pretty nice, especially with those concave tops to keep your thumbs in place.
.
A few things to note are that there's no NFC compatibility, no rumble, no motion controls, and to get this working you have to first turn wired pro controller connection on in the setting with a different controller, THEN slide the Switch into place, and don't try updating the controller or it will go out of sync after failing. So it basically just feeds off the battery of the Switch for power, but it didn't seem to hog much power compared to playing with other controllers as far as I've noticed.
.
You'll see the Wii U gamepad here not only for a size comparison but also a reminder. The Switch can be used not just as a console, a handheld, or a portable console via tabletop mode. It can also be used for off TV play! It's a pretty limited concept, sure, but if you just want to watch something on your TV while you play then it's great to have around the house. It's not going to be a great travel companion due to its size and awkward shape, and while on the TV you might as well use a pro controller, but just playing off your TV at home... this thing is pretty nice.
.
One word of warning: Your Switch might be a little tough to get out of this thing. That's nice to know it won't come falling out, even if you tip it upside down, but it can be a little scary prying it out of there. I'm hoping worst case scenario will be that the accessory breaks.
.
Thoughts on this... thing?

1 ottobre 1954
IBM annuncia il computer Modello 705
L'IBM 705 è un computer di prima generazione, a valvole termoioniche. I primi esemplari vengono consegnati nel 1956. E' una macchina character-oriented (ovvero in cui il terminale comunica con l'elaboratore principale un carattere alla volta, contrariamente a quanto avviene nelle macchine block-oriented, in cui il terminale trasferisce blocchi di dati) con caratteri a 7 bit e parole a 35 bit (per contenere 5 caratteri).
Il 705 Modello I viene equipaggiato con una capacità di archiviazione pari a 20.000 caratteri e costa circa 590.000 dollari. Il modello II e III hanno una capacità di archiviazione pari, rispettivamente, a 40.000 ed 80.000 caratteri. Può moltiplicare due numeri composti da dieci cifre in soli .0024 secondi.
Il 705 è il primo computer distribuito commercialmente ad essere equipaggiato con una memoria a nucleo magnetico. Sostituisce l'IBM 702, che utilizzava una memoria costituita da un complesso di tubi a raggi catodici, in cui la sola unità aritmetica necessitava di 1.700 tubi a vuoto.

caption.text: 🤘🏼🎧❤️ #theyoungprofessionals #lanadelrey #videogames

Ieri ho deciso di aprire una nuova specie di rubrica che intitolerò : " Giochi epici che avrei dovuto giocare all'uscita ma che non ho mai giocato fino ad oggi''. Il protagonista di oggi e' Uncharted 4 A Thief's End. Wow. Sono rimasto davvero sorpreso dal prodotto di Naughty Dog, e mai avrei pensato che la saga di Uncharted potesse superare la bellezza e epicità raggiunta nel 2. Iniziando dai paesaggi , Uncharted 4 spinge PS4 a livelli mai visti primi. E' un gioco bello da vedere ma soprattutto ti dà l' impressione di essere vivo davanti i tuoi occhi. Per non parlare dell' Oceano e di come Naughty Dog abbiato lavorato per renderlo un paradiso per i giocatori. La chiusura delle storie legate a ciascun personaggio e' da Oscar , e ammetto di aver versato un paio di lacrime durante le scene finali. Questo e' l' esempio vivente di come un gioco passi da semplice mezzo di intrattenimento a vera e propria arte. Un applauso

Yesterday I decided to start a new journey which i named: "Epic games that I should have played when they came out but never did until now". Today's protagonist is Uncharted 4 A Thief's End. Wow. I was really surprised by Naughty Dog's product, and I never thought that the Uncharted saga could overcome the beauty and epicness achieved in second game. Starting from the landscapes, Uncharted 4 pushes PS4 to levels never seen before. It is so beautiful that there are times where the game almost seems to gain a life of his own. All the stories related to the different characters are closed wonderfully , and I have to admit that I cried a little during the ending scenes. This is the example of how a simple tool of entertainment can become art. Well done Naughty Dog.
